4-linux-gnu.so</code> looks for <code>libstdc++.so.6</code> in <code>/usr/lib64</code> and does not look for <code>LD_LIBRARY_PATH</code>.</p>\n<p>Is there a way to fix this without recompiling or rewriting <code>/usr/lib64</code>?</p>", "body_text": "I installed CPU caffe2 with anaconda (conda install -c caffe2 caffe2-gcc4.8).\nThe problem is that caffe2_pybind11_state.cpython-36m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so looks for libstdc++.so.6 in /usr/lib64 and does not look for LD_LIBRARY_PATH.\nIs there a way to fix this without recompiling or rewriting /usr/lib64?", "body": "I installed CPU caffe2 with anaconda (`conda install -c caffe2 caffe2-gcc4.8`).\r\n\r\nThe problem is that `caffe2_pybind11_state.cpython-36m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so` looks for `libstdc++.so.6` in `/usr/lib64` and does not look for `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`.\r\n\r\nIs there a way to fix this without recompiling or rewriting `/usr/lib64`?"}